  associate professor of mechanical engineering  has received the VMI awards faculty development leave for fall term to develop a comprehensive and integrated  Introduction to Mechanical Engineering  course  The Ayres faculty development leave has been awarded to Lt  Col  Roger Thompson  associate professor of English  to conduct research and draft chapters for a book on Ralph Waldo Emerson and the history of rhetoric in the fall  Four professors have received Jackson Hope faculty development leaves  Lt  Col  Elena Andreeva  associate professor of history  will conduct research and work on a book on the Orient in Russian culture next spring  Col  Tappey Jones  professor of chemistry  will pursue multidisciplinary studies in insect plant interactions and insect olfaction during the 2007 08 year  Lt  Col  Stan Smith  associate professor of chemistry  will conduct research on the synthesis of heterocyclic molecules during the spring  and Col  Mark Wilkinson  professor of history  will pursue language studies and work on a book tentatively titled  At the Crossroads  Shanghai in Chinese American Relations  1937 1950  during the fall in China  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 